notes: On 16 March 2020, Armenia declared a nationwide state of emergency from 16 March to 14 April to contain the spread of coronavirus. Protests, strikes and public events were prohibited. On 31 March 2020, the lockdown was prolonged for another 10 days. The travel between the regions was tightened and police checkpoints set. On 4 May, the lockdown was lifted and the work of the most business were resumed but with obligation to wear masks. On 14 May 2020, another lockdown was declared as the outbreak developed further. It was prolonged on 13 June 2020 and 12 August 2020. On 11 September, state of emergency ended but mask obligation and social distancing were kept in place for public spaces.
